Anonymous Wed 04 Aug 2021 22:07:45 No.40678281 Report
Quoted By: >>40679789
>>40676784
I'm unsure of it as a plot device, per se. A character attribute, yes, but as a serious issue addressed /by/ the plot, it's not to be tread lightly. You don't cure it with medicine; realistically, if it develops after childhood following a majorly traumatic event, the prospect for any return-to-zero status quo is negative. Children can grow into it without even being aware of it if they repress their knowledge of the event(s). In adolescents, it can and will govern nearly every aspect of their psychological, emotional, and physical development without careful, interceding therapy. This anon
>>40676889
explained it well in allegorical detail. It's not just a psychological response to being bullied or sexually abused as memed by Dick Wolf. Ptsd encompasses a broad range of nervous & somatic symptoms, the most consistent being sundry ranges of anxiety disorders, major depression, and coping mechanisms that encompass the meat of the DSM-5. The Anon I quoted described some aspects of hyper-vigilance, an umbrella term given to the symptoms responsible for the behavioral tendencies most readily observable/diagnosable in people with PTSD. Aptly named, because that state of fight or flight terror, environmental unrest, and total mental occupation can't be turned off; it never goes away. Sufferers experience sensory and emotional burnout frequently, even if they're physically adapted from childhood. They're prone to disassociative states, total emotional vacancy (or overbearing sensitivity before vacancy), and social rejection resulting from all of the above.

Jacklin handles it well; Dave in Altruistic Intent is another good example, constantly struggling with his trauma and moral compass to the extent that his love for his daughters (as opposed to pure parental instinct) was ambiguous enough to me, it felt like an intended plot device. My favorite stories with PTSD-affected protags don't address/acknowledge it forthright, but it's omnipresent (WKW & HATSx).
